net: add MPTCP v1 support

This patch adds support for Multipath TCP v1 (RFC 8684) to the
kernel networking stack.

MPTCP allows a single TCP connection to use multiple paths
simultaneously, providing:
- Increased throughput through link aggregation
- Seamless handover between networks
- Improved resilience to link failures

The implementation includes:
- MPTCP option parsing and generation
- Subflow management
- Path manager interface
- Scheduler for packet scheduling across subflows

